debugger-error-integration — Phase 3: *error* interception + vl-catch-all-apply
================================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 3)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-spec.org (§10)
  issues/open/debugger-snapshot-stepping.issue (prerequisite — Phase 2)

Context
-------

AutoLISP has no condition system — only the `*error*` function-valued global
and vl-catch-all-apply / vl-catch-all-error-p / vl-catch-all-error-message.
The runtime already signals a structured `autolisp-runtime-error` (code /
message / details / call-stack, api.lisp:87) and tracks per-session `errno`
(api.lisp:456). This phase wires those error paths into the debugger.

NOTE: verify at kickoff whether a `*error*`-handler hook already exists in
the runtime; if not, adding it is part of this phase.

Scope / deliverables
--------------------

1. `*error*` interception (spec §10.1): on the uncaught-error path, build a
   snapshot at the error point, send `:unhandled-error`, block on inbound.
   Resolutions:
   - :continue-with-error  — invoke the user's real `*error*` (default).
   - :continue-with-return — supply a value for the erroring form; offered
     ONLY for form-internal errors (e.g. (/ 1 0)), never host primitives.
   - :abort — unwind cleanly, restoring system variables.
   Show the user's `*error*` handler as a frame so it can be stepped into.

2. vl-catch-all-apply (spec §10.2): record each catch as a frame in the
   per-thread `catch-stack`; with "break on caught error" enabled (default
   off) send `:caught-error` before the AutoLISP error object is returned.

3. No restarts surfaced in the AutoLISP-facing UI (spec §10.3); the CL
   condition system is used internally only.

Acceptance
----------

- (/ 1 0) breaks into the debugger with the erroring form highlighted;
  :abort restores sysvars; :continue-with-return supplies a value.
- A vl-catch-all-apply frame appears in the snapshot's catch-stack; break-on-
  caught fires when enabled.
- FiveAM tests; `*version*` bumped.

* Resolution (triage 2026-07-23)

Shipped: error.lisp/session.lisp — :continue-with-return, break-on-caught, the catch stack, §10 handler integration; hardened further by error-while-debugging.issue (closed).
